In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims November 17 to November 23, 2013, as American Education Week. He emphasizes the importance of education as a pillar of democracy and an opportunity for American citizens. The President acknowledges the milestones achieved by students and expresses admiration and support for educators. He highlights the role that parents, mentors, community leaders, and business owners play in supporting education. The President also discusses the administration's commitment to reducing college costs, making high-quality early education accessible to all children, and strengthening programs in science, technology, engineering, and mathematics. The proclamation concludes with a call for Americans to observe the week by supporting local schools through appropriate activities and programs.